						<summary>

						<p>States that <hi rend="bold">Muppa Nāganāyaka</hi> made a gift of land as emoluments to the <hi rend="italic">Sānis</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Mānis</hi> as also for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Rāmīśvara of <hi rend="bold">Chunumūru</hi> and for feeding ten Brahmins in a <hi rend="italic">choultry</hi> in the said village. Mentions <hi rend="bold">Goṅkarāja</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Velanāṇḍu.</hi></p>						

